# Build-time toolchain for the frozen Windows ship build. Compiled (WITH hashes) to
# requirements-build-win.txt:
#   pip-compile --generate-hashes --allow-unsafe -o requirements-build-win.txt requirements-build.in
# --allow-unsafe is required: PyInstaller pulls in setuptools, which pip-compile classes as "unsafe"
# and would otherwise leave unpinned. To move a transitive pin (e.g. for an advisory), add
# --upgrade-package <name> — a plain re-compile keeps whatever the lock already pins (RELEASE.md §1).
# Installed into the clean build venv alongside requirements-win.txt so PyInstaller runs offline from
# vendor/wheels. PyInstaller is build-only — it is never bundled into the app. Inno Setup is a
# separate native tool (not a wheel); its version is pinned in DEPENDENCIES.md.
pyinstaller>=6.21,<7
